# SDK Package Conventions

## Package Size

- Minimize dependencies. Each package should have as few runtime dependencies as possible.
- `@aip/core` has zero runtime dependencies (types, constants, error classes only).
- `@aip/verify` depends only on `jose` and `@aip/core`.

## Runtime Compatibility

- `@aip/core` and `@aip/verify` must work in all runtimes: Node.js, Deno, Bun, Cloudflare Workers, Vercel Edge.
- Do not use Node.js-specific APIs (`fs`, `path`, `crypto` from `node:`) in these packages.
- Use Web Crypto API (`crypto.subtle`) or `jose` abstractions instead.
- Node.js-specific packages (`@aip/express`) may use Node.js APIs.

## Build & Exports

- Build with `tsup`. Output both ESM and CJS.
- Single `src/index.ts` entry point per package.
- `package.json` must specify `exports`, `main`, `module`, `types` fields.

## Public API

- Every exported function, class, and type must have JSDoc with `@example`.
- Err on the side of fewer exports. Internal helpers are not exported.
- Use explicit named exports — no `export *`.

## Error Handling

- All SDK error classes extend `AipError` from `@aip/core`.
- Error classes must include a `code` property (string enum) for programmatic handling.
- User-facing error messages must be clear and suggest a fix.

## Versioning

- Follow semantic versioning strictly.
- Breaking changes require a major version bump.
- Maintain a CHANGELOG.md in each package root.
